	<text>
		<body>
			<p><!--{{Alexander Kirk}}, (Telegramm), <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName> über <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/2800866/brussels.html">Brüssel</placeName>, 8.2.1940, Teil 2,
        S. 1f., Teil 3, 1f.</p>
      <p>: Dokument 860C.4016/603</p--></p>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19400208_01.jpg"/>
			<p>The <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-423">Jewish authorities</orgName> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName> who are competent only for <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Reich</term> territory have little precise <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-220" type="subject">information</term> concerning <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">conditions</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> although the following is their understanding of
				the situation in that area based upon such meager reliable date as they have been able to obtain:</p>
			<p>A mass <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-575" type="subject">transfer of the Jews</term> in the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3096472/katowice.html">Kattowitz</placeName> region which was threatened has been postponed at least
				until <date when="1940-03">March</date>. It is not known here to what extent the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-575" type="subject">transfer of Jews</term> from other regions is still
				being carried out under present conditions although it is understood that considerable numbers of <pb n="2"
					facs="EHRI-DR-19400208_02.jpg"/>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> are being expelled from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html">Lodz</placeName> and are being sent east. The situation of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> appears to be at its worst in the vicinity
				of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName> where it is said that they are being subjected to
				particularly brutal <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-601" type="subject">treatment </term>by the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-360" type="subject">party</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> Guards. It is also stated that <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> have been sent to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName> in unheated <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">trains</term> with the result that cases of freezing
				to death have been reported. [...]</p>
			<pb n="3" facs="EHRI-DR-19400208_03.jpg"/>
			<p>While reports which are mostly second hand are received in sufficient quantity to demonstrate that unquestionably great suffering is
				being endured by the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> and by large groups
				of <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_poles">Poles</term> it is pointed out in local <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans"
					>German</term> circles that the current hardships, which on the one hand are inevitable as a result of the military campaign and
				of the redistribution of [Auslassung in der Originalvorlage], pale by comparison with those which existed in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> following the last war and that on the other hand
				some of the stern measures now being taken by the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1032" type="subject"
					>German authorities</term> are necessary for the purpose of eliminating the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-527" type="subject">criminal elements</term> released from <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-651" type="subject">jails</term> at the beginning of the war and for the
				restoration of order following the <pb n="4" facs="EHRI-DR-19400208_04.jpg"/> complete collapse of the <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_poles">Polish</term> state system.</p>
